[[File:Gout tuber strategy (3).png|thumb|right|Snake boxing method area. Facing south-east]]
Players that do not have the Defence levels or resources to do the tank method can still easily collect gout tubers using the snake boxing method. This method requires very little resources and Defence levels. The player will be boxing a level 5 [[snake]], so any usable armour that provides some level of melee defence can be used. 

The two dense jungle section shown on the map will be cut. These two sections are in close proximity to a snake spawn. The player will attack the snake once and then begin cutting the dense jungle. The snake will continue to attack the player and maintain aggression. As the player cuts the jungle and receives monster events, the monster will attack the player once, and then stop. Due to the snake maintaining aggression, the stronger monsters from the jungle events will not be able to continue to attack the player. 

The player needs to bring a [[fun weapon]] or runes to cast a non-damaging spell, such as [[weaken]]. The player will equip the fun weapon to attack the snake, reducing the chance of accidentally killing the snake. Higher level players may require additional melee reducing gear, such as the [[berserker necklace]], in order to prevent accidentally killing the snake. 

Alternatively players can bring equipment reducing magic attack to -64 and runes to cast a combat spell to [[splash]] on the snake. This is a more consistent way of attacking the snake without killing it. 

When cutting the jungle the player should not stand on the square beside both of the jungle sections. This square causes the snake to get pushed to the side, and get stuck behind jungle sections when a monster event attacks the player.

Using antidote++ is still required, as the monster events can still inflict poison on the player. Bring a stack of noted antidote++ and coins and use Aisles to un-note them. 

A small amount of food is recommended as backup. 
